T*
(Introduction to Algebra: Expressions and Equations) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Overview) Tj
T*
(This lesson introduces the fundamental concepts of algebra, focusing on algebraic) Tj
T*
(expressions and equations. Students will learn how to identify, simplify, and manipulate) Tj
T*
(expressions, as well as how to solve basic linear equations. The goal is to build a) Tj
T*
(solid foundation in algebraic thinking and problem-solving skills.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Learning Objectives) Tj
T*
(- Understand what algebraic expressions and equations are.) Tj
T*
(- Learn to simplify algebraic expressions using basic operations.) Tj
T*
(- Develop skills to solve simple linear equations.) Tj
T*
(- Apply algebraic methods to solve real-world problems.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Lesson Content) Tj
T*
(What is Algebra?) Tj
T*
(Algebra is a branch of mathematics that uses symbols, usually letters, to represent) Tj
T*
(numbers and quantities in formulas and equations. These symbols allow us to write) Tj
T*
(general rules and solve problems involving unknown values. Instead of working with) Tj
T*
(specific numbers, algebra works with variables, which makes it a powerful tool for) Tj
T*
(solving a wide range of problems.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Algebraic Expressions) Tj
T*
(An algebraic expression is a combination of numbers, variables \(like x or y\), and) Tj
T*
(arithmetic operations \(such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division\). For) Tj
T*
(example, 3x + 5 is an algebraic expression. Expressions do not have an equals sign \(=\).) Tj
T*
(They can be simplified by combining like terms and applying arithmetic rules.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Simplifying Algebraic Expressions) Tj
T*
(Simplifying expressions means rewriting them in a simpler or more compact form without) Tj
T*
(changing their value. This often involves combining like termsâ€”terms that have the same) Tj
T*
(variable raised to the same powerâ€”and performing arithmetic operations. For example, in) Tj
T*
(the expression 2x + 3x + 4, the terms 2x and 3x can be combined to make 5x, so the) Tj
T*
(simplified expression is 5x + 4.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Algebraic Equations) Tj
T*
(An algebraic equation states that two expressions are equal, using the equals sign \(=\).) Tj
T*
(For example, 2x + 3 = 11 is an equation. The goal is to find the value of the variable) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
