T*
() Tj
T*
(Lesson Vocabulary) Tj
T*
(- Variable: A symbol, usually a letter, that represents an unknown number or value.) Tj
T*
(- Expression: A combination of numbers, variables, and operations without an equals) Tj
T*
(sign.) Tj
T*
(- Equation: A mathematical statement showing that two expressions are equal, containing) Tj
T*
(an equals sign.) Tj
T*
(- Like Terms: Terms in an expression that have the same variable raised to the same) Tj
T*
(power and can be combined.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Combining unlike terms, such as adding x and xÂ˛.) Tj
T*
(- Forgetting to perform the same operation on both sides of the equation.) Tj
T*
(- Dropping the minus sign when moving terms across the equals sign.) Tj
T*
(- Not checking the solution by substituting it back into the equation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Review Questions) Tj
T*
(- What is the difference between an expression and an equation?) Tj
T*
(- Simplify the expression: 5y + 3 - 2y + 6.) Tj
T*
(- Solve the equation: 4x + 7 = 19.) Tj
T*
(- Why must you perform the same operation on both sides of an equation?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Quick Check) Tj
T*
(Use the review questions above to confirm your understanding before moving to practice.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Independent Practice) Tj
T*
(- Simplify: 6a - 2 + 4a + 9.) Tj
T*
(- Solve for x: 5x - 8 = 12.) Tj
T*
(- Simplify: 3m + 2n - m + 7n.) Tj
T*
(- Solve for y: 7y + 3 = 31.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Summary) Tj
T*
(Algebra is a key area of mathematics that uses variables to represent unknown values.) Tj
T*
(Understanding how to work with algebraic expressions and equations is essential for) Tj
T*
